section.section:
"Retirement community" does not include:
A freestanding nursing home, as defined in § 19-1401 of the Health - General Article, that is licensed by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene;
A State facility, as defined in § 10-101 of the Health - General Article;
A program licensed by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene under Title 7 or Title 10 of the Health - General Article;
A freestanding hospice care program regulated by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene under Title 19, Subtitle 9 of the Health - General Article;
A freestanding day care center for the elderly regulated by the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene under Title 14, Subtitle 2 of the Health - General Article;
A retirement community that is owned by or affiliated with a church or religious organization;
A cooperative housing corporation organized under Title 5, Subtitle 6B of the Corporations and Associations Article and certified as a continuing care provider under Title 10, Subtitle 4 of the Human Services Article and separate entities certified as continuing care providers under Title 10, Subtitle 4 of the Human Services Article that provide services to residents of a cooperative housing corporation; or
A condominium organized under Title 11 of the Real Property Article and certified as a continuing care provider under Title 10, Subtitle 4 of the Human Services Article and separate entities certified as continuing care providers under Title 10, Subtitle 4 of the Human Services Article that provide services to residents of a condominium.
